Count 1 - 1st degree recklessly endangering safety - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of six (6) years.  Three (3) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's asssessment process;
2) Have no contact with the victim, Charles Krummel;
3) Continue with counseling presently enrolled in;
4) Take medications as prescribed and in prescribed doses;
5) Provide DNA sample;
6) Pay costs of action;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Count 2 - Criminal damage to property - Defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for eight (8) months, under the Huber Law, to commence on 02-18-15 by 5:00 p.m.  Defendant is given credit for eighty-three (83) days time already served.  Court costs are waived.   
